you can use scp

to donwload from a remote hosts just run:

scp myuser@hostname:~/myfile.txt ~/Documents

no need to access via ssh before

this will download the myfile.txt from the remote host (from home: ~/) to the local path: ~/Documents



To upload to another machine:

scp ~/myfile.txt myuser@hostname:~/

this will send myfile.txt to the home directory of the remote host

password will be asked 
